75int
76nvif_client_init(const char *driver, const char *name, u64 device,
77 const char *cfg, const char *dbg, struct nvif_client *client)
78{
79 struct {
80 struct nvif_ioctl_v0 ioctl;
81 struct nvif_ioctl_nop_v0 nop;
82 } args = {};
83 int ret, i;
84
85 ret = nvif_object_init(NULL, 0, 0, NULL, 0, &client->object);
86 if (ret)
87 return ret;
88
89 client->object.client = client;
90 client->object.handle = ~0;
91 client->route = NVIF_IOCTL_V0_ROUTE_NVIF;
92 client->super = true;
93
94 for (i = 0, ret = -EINVAL; (client->driver = nvif_drivers[i]); i++) {
95 if (!driver || !strcmp(client->driver->name, driver)) {
96 ret = client->driver->init(name, device, cfg, dbg,
97 &client->object.priv);
98 if (!ret || driver)
99 break;
100 }
101 }
102
103 if (ret == 0) {
104 ret = nvif_client_ioctl(client, &args, sizeof(args));
105 client->version = args.nop.version;
106 }
107
108 if (ret)
109 nvif_client_fini(client);
110 return ret;
111}
